==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Integer
<hw>In"te*ger</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>integer</ets> untouched, whole, entire. See <er>Entire</er>.]</ety>
<def>A complete entity; a whole number, in contradistinction to a
fraction or a mixed number.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Complex integer</b></col> <fld>(Theory of Numbers)</fld>,
<cd>an expression of the form <mathex>a + b⟦root⟧-1</mathex>, where
<it>a</it> and <it>b</it> are real integers.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Integrability</ent>⟦br⟧
